      <BlogCrossLinks title="Words Starting With Post" />

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Starting with POST in Scrabble</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-20">June 20, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        POST is a powerful Scrabble prefix that combines a valid standalone word (6 points) with dozens of longer extensions. The POST- prefix covers timing-related vocabulary (POSTPONE, POSTDATE), mail-related words (POSTMAN, POSTMARK), and positional terms (POSTERIOR, POSTLUDE). At 4 letters, POST is shorter than TRANS or UNDER, leaving 3 tiles for the root — making 7-letter bingos more achievable from your rack alone.
      </p>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">80+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid POST Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">19</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Highest Base Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avg Score (7-letter)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4–12</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter Range</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card Grid: Most Useful POST Words -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 Best for Bingos</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POSTING (7) · POSTERN (7) · POSTURE (7) · POSTAGE (7) · POSTMAN (7)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ Highest Scoring</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POSTFIX (19) · POSTBOX (18) · POSTMARK (16) · POSTPUNK (16) · POSTPONE (12)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📝 Most Common</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POSTPONE · POSTCARD · POSTER · POSTAL · POSTMAN · POSTMARK · POSTURE · POSTWAR</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 Easy to Build</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POST · POSTS · POSTED · POSTER · POSTAL · POSTERN · POSTING · POSTAGE</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">POST Words by Length (4–6 Letters)</h2>

      <p>Short POST words give you flexibility on the board. POST itself is only 4 letters and scores 6 points — a clean, common play that opens up massive extension potential on future turns. The 5–6 letter POST words are common enough to play directly from your rack.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">4–5 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POST (6pts) · POSTS (7pts) · POSTY (10pts, SOWPODS)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">6 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POSTED (9pts) · POSTER (8pts) · POSTAL (8pts) · POSTIL (8pts) · POSTIC (10pts)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Bingo-Length POST Words (7 Letters)</h2>

      <p>Seven-letter POST words earn the 50-point bingo bonus. With 4 tiles committed to the prefix, you need just 3 more letters to complete the play. Common endings like -ING, -AGE, -ERN, -URE, and -MAN combine naturally with POST.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">7-Letter Bingos</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POSTING (10+50) · POSTERN (9+50) · POSTURE (9+50) · POSTAGE (10+50) · POSTMAN (11+50) · POSTMEN (11+50) · POSTBAG (12+50) · POSTIES (9+50)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">POST uses 4 of your 7 tiles, leaving <span class="text-white font-medium">3 tiles for the suffix</span>. Common endings that complete a bingo: -ING (POSTING), -AGE (POSTAGE), -ERN (POSTERN), -URE (POSTURE), -MAN (POSTMAN). If you hold P-O-S-T plus any of these letter combos, you have a bingo.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">POST Words (8+ Letters)</h2>

      <p>Longer POST words are typically formed by extending an existing POST on the board. This is where the "play POST early" strategy pays off — your opponent cannot easily predict which extension you are building toward.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">8 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POSTCARD (13) · POSTCODE (13) · POSTDATE (11) · POSTDOCS (13) · POSTFIRE (13) · POSTFIX (19) · POSTFORM (15) · POSTHEAT (13) · POSTHOLE (13) · POSTLUDE (11) · POSTMARK (16) · POSTPONE (12) · POSTRACE (12) · POSTSHOW (16) · POSTTEST (10)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">9+ Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POSTCARDS · POSTCODES · POSTPONED · POSTERIOR · POSTMARKS · POSTNASAL · POSTNATAL · POSTSCRIPT · POSTURING · POSTWOMAN · POSTMORTEM</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: POST Words on Premium Squares</h2>

      <p>POST is a setup prefix — you play it early for modest points, then extend it massively on a later turn. Here is how tournament players maximize POST words across the board.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play POST as an opener or early word:</span> POST on the center star scores 12 (DW). On your next turn, extend it to POSTING, POSTAL, or POSTPONE. Your opponent cannot easily block a back-extension because dozens of valid suffixes exist. The 6-point investment becomes a 60+ point return.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target POSTFIX for maximum value:</span> POSTFIX scores 19 points base — the highest for any common POST word. With the X on a TL square, that X alone contributes 24 points. Position the word so X lands on Triple Letter for devastating results (potentially 40+ points before word multipliers).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Extend existing words with POST-:</span> If PONE is on the board, adding POST in front creates POSTPONE. If MARK is there, POSTMARK appears. If DATE exists, POSTDATE is valid. Scan the board for 4–6 letter words that POST can prefix — the combinations are more common than you think.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use POSTS for double-duty:</span> Adding S to POST creates POSTS (7pts) which can extend in both directions — POST+S now, then later pre-extend with a letter or suffix at the back. POSTS is also useful as a parallel play, forming cross-words with each letter touching adjacent tiles.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">POST vs BACK: Prefix Comparison</h2>

      <p>Both POST and BACK are 4-letter prefixes that form compound words. Here is how they compare for Scrabble strategy.</p>

      <!-- Comparison Cards -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ POST Advantages</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid standalone (6pts). Contains S (common tile, 1pt). Many timing-related extensions. POSTFIX has X for high scoring. Predictable suffixes (-ING, -AGE, -MAN).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ POST Drawbacks</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Fewer total words than DE or CO (~80 vs 1000+). P tile is medium-frequency (2 per bag). Most high-value POST words need 8+ letters. Predictable to opponents who may block extensions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚠️ Pro Tip</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">POST is most effective as a <span class="text-white font-medium">two-turn strategy</span>: play POST on turn 1 for 6–12 points, then extend to an 8-letter word on turn 2 for 50+ points. If you can score both, that is 60+ points from a single 4-letter investment. Do not force an 8-letter POST bingo from your rack alone unless it is clearly available.</p>
      </div>

